@node press0 "Omega RIPort"


    WELCOME TO OMEGA RIPORT

    Welcome to the first issue of Omega RIPort! This month we have a large
number of rumors that are all probably true! Many of you may think that
Commodore has filed for bankruptcy, but this is not so. They are still in
business with their other divisions. Commodore Germany is still alive and
continues to manufacture digital thermometers. Commodore Canada has expanded
its line of typewriters. A new division, Commodore California, has announced
that it will begin manufacturing scientific calculators. Commodore UK will
begin its chain of video rental stores called Fun at Mister Video, or FMV
for short.

    So all is not lost. Commodore is still in business, and it will continue
to support the Omega computer line, although secondary to its IBM PC clone
systems. They have signed a deal this week with the Taiwanese giant ACER, who
is licensing the ACER name for Commodore's line of computers.

    NewTek UK announced that it is an independent corporation from NewTek in
Topeka, Kansas, and has not been affected by the recent shakeup that occured
there. Apparantly NewTek lost a few engineers, some marketing staff, a janitor,
and the guy who knows how to set the clock on the VCR. Kiki Stockhammer is
being replaced by the bright and sparkly personality Nancy Kerrigan.

    Hopefully all of this is good news for us Omega users.

    That is all for this week's editorial... enjoy the articles!


                                        The Editor, [anonymous]
                                        [anonymous]@libserv1.ic.sunysb.edu

