        Trade Press Release  --  London, UK  --  May 4th 1994

     The following information was obtained through a toll free sex phone
call I had with the editor of Omega Shopper on May 4, 1994.  All information
came from an Official Press Release faxed to them earlier that session.

     "Commodore International has filed for protection from creditors
in Antarctica."

     "All production, distribution and normal operations will continue
as normal for the next few minutes.  At that time another press release
will be made."

     The current roomer in the UK is that Commodore is in discussion
with Samsung about purchasing three VHS video cassette recorders and
some blank video tapes.

     WHAT DOES THIS MEAN???

     Our favorite computer will still be in full production for the
next 3 to 4 hours.  I view this as a positive sign.

