@node press4 "Omega RIPort - Edited by David Tiberio"
@toc main

                   - COMMODORE FUNERAL PARTY -
              West Chester, PA  --  April 30th 1994

Don't know if this is news, but on Saturday, April 30, there was a
Commodore wake at Randal's house.  Almost all of the current Commodore
engineering employees and large numbers of former engineering folk were
in attendance.  Cultural activities included burning Medhi in effigy,
a keyboard smash, and the Bryce / Randal two-player lemmings world
championship.

A videotape of the event was taken, which caused a lot of remeniscing
about some of the more interesting events of the past 7 or 8 years.  Here's
one of the more fun stories:

Property passes:
        There was a rule at Commodore that whenever you brought in personal
property that you had to get a property pass.  This was so that when you
took the property out, they knew it was yours and not the company's.  It
turned out that the morning receptionist, Dotty, was absolutely vigilant
about making sure that one filled out a property pass.  The security guards
were not at all vigilant about making sure that you had a property pass for
everything that you removed.  This alone resulted in many amusing anomolys.
(for instance, I had collected at least 20 property passes for a walkman
that I used to carry in and out of work each day).  To make things more
interesting, Dotty didn't really look at what you wrote on the property
pass, she just insisted that you get one.  This lead people to fill out
property passes for odd things:

        Actual items people had gotten property passes for:

                A Boeing 747
                cbmvax
                the speed bumps
                A Cray Y-MP (in case Commodore ever got one)

        At least three people were forced to get property passes for
empty boxes.  One of them insisted that they were donating the boxes to
Commodore, but to no avail.

        I'm half tempted to write a book with all of these stories.  I could
call it "Chicken lip tales".  (We used to call the logo the "chicken lips".)

                                                        Joe (augi).

@endnode
