@node press5 "Omega RIPort - Edited by David Tiberio"
@toc main

                   - MATELLL TO BUY OMEGA TECHNOLOGY -
          Trade Press Release  --  Troy, NY  --  May 5th 1994

Matelll Corp., a well know toy manufacturer, announced it's intention to
purchase Omega design technology from the now defunct Commodore Business
machines. Matelll feels that the Omega remains a viable computer able to
compete with currently marketed computer systems. In order to provide for
the future, a number of upgrades to current Omega systems has been
announced.

New Omega Mouse
The new mouse will be modelled after a real rodent to provide a 'natural'
feel. The new mouse will be covered in an artificial fur that is
indistinguishable from real mink. As an added bonus, the new mouse will
'deposit' a small, round candy treat on the mouse pad each time the new
fourth mouse button is pressed (mice to be refilled only by an authorized
service center).

Light Brite Interface.
A new graphical display tool known as 'Lite Brite' will be incorporated
into the AGA chip set. This will allow users to create breathtaking 320 peg
by 200 peg colour images with a clarity not possible on other peg displays.
The AAA chip set will carry this tool to the max by enhancing resolution to
a stunning 640 x380 pegs and will add an additional 3 new colours: Violet,
Mustard, and Neon Green. This upgrade will occupy the video slot of the
A-2000, A-3000, and A-4000 systems.

Easy Bake Oven side car.
For those late nights and long days spent bent over the keyboard an Easy
Bake Oven attachment is planned for the current Omega line. There will be
two versions; one will interface via PCMCIA, and another will interface via
ZORRO card expansion. Each oven will come with an initial 10 cake packets
and a special offer to order an additional 20 packets at a discount via
Omega/Matelll tech support offices. Free sprinkles will be sent to the
first 500 users to register their systems for warranty. Cake mixes for the
standard Easy bake oven will not operate within the Omega Easy Bake Oven
and any attempt to use a mix without the Omega logo on the package will
void your warranty. Cakes are licensed for one user per system per oven.

New system libraries will include:
Speak and Spell.lib
Barnyard Friends.lib

Watch for these new systems in your favorite computer dealers retail space
or nearest toy store. To be sure you're getting the new product just look
for the Matelll inside sticker.


Disclaimer: Yes this is a parody, and no, I don't want to be flamed. I've
had various Commodore and Omega products for 13+ years now and I find the
whole Commodore story sadly amusing. C'est le vie. Guess I'll just have to
settle with my Mac. :)

--
Anthony Bugera

