@node press9 "Omega RIPort - Edited by David Tiberio"
@toc main

Utilities Unlimited creates the first Omega outside of Commodore.

Jim Drew, president of Utilities Unlimited (UU), announced today, that he has
obtained the rights to produce the Omega.  This announcement shocked millions
of Omega owners, after just learning that Commodore International Limited had
folded.  Mr. Drew also announced a new machine.  This annoucement gave Omega
followers the leader that they were looking for, and immediately began raving
about the new machine, and what a sucky job Jim was doing at marketing it.

Since UU does not have the technology to produce custom ASICs in-house, they
reverse engineered the Omega's custom chips, and have opted for a more low
tech, low cost design.  That's right.. he has 15,000 PALs all piggy backed,
and wire wrapped to each other, on a double sided circuit board the size of
your head.  Jim preferred to use both extra board space, and unique 3D
soldering techniques to obtain this product.  He is in the process of
training his other employees in this wonderful art.  This gives UU the
ability to emulate producting Omegas for a fraction of the cost that they
were being produced for when Commodore was really manufacturing them.  The
new quad-060 "Omega", which has been renamed to the "Chauna", in honor of his
wife, whose body the case work resembles, marks the first time that the
OmegaOS will be run on multiple processors, and the second time, that the
Omega has been in a sexy case.  Mr. Drew reportedly divorced his wife, as he
become confused over which case work belonged to whom, and inadvertantly
soldered an 060 to her forehead.  Jim later stated that it was only running
on _one_ processor, and the others where emulating it.  When asked whether he
was talking about his ex-wife or "Chauna", he again got confused.  What
surprised this reporter was the fact that the emulated code ran 4 times
faster than the non-emulated code on the same speed processor.  This was due
to the math code rewrite in the emulation, causing the 060 Omega to
outperform a Cray MPX-1.  As an added bonus, the new machines contain 20 ROM
sockets to insert the ROMs of the machine you wanted emulated.  Just insert
the ROM(s), and the new machine detects and emulates the computer
automatically.

When Chauna was asked how she felt about the whole ordeal, she stated she was
having hot flashes.  Jim later fixed this by affixing a large heatsink to her
forehead.  Jim reconsiled the divorce when he found he could reboot Chauna
any time she didn't do what he asked her.  When asked whether he was talking
about the "real" Chauna, or the "Chauna", he again got confused.

This marvel will be shown at the next CES, provided that they can find enough
free electrical sockets, and fans.

[Editor's note: let's hope he remembers to bring the software this time. DT]

Millions of followers made the journey to Lake Havasu, Arizona, to kiss the
ground that Mr. Drew developed the new machine on.  This created more
moisture than Arizona was used to, and screwed up the weather while it all
evaporated.  This caused the local Indians to regard Mr. Drew as a rain-god,
give him the honorary name of "sockittoempocket", and carved a statue in his
honor.

It is rumoured that by hitting a special sequence of keystrokes, that the new
machine will emulate Medhi Ali, by becoming distant, unfocused, and inept.
This reporter, however, was unable to duplicate this at the time of this
writing.

This new machine is available from UU immediately.  Call for pricing:
1-900-IMA-DORK.

William J. Coldwell - Omega RIPort affiliate reporter

